__SqlaTable__.sql:
SELECT CONCAT(repository_owner, '/', repository_name) AS repository, created_at, merged_at, closed_at 
FROM pull_requests

SELECT
    CONCAT(repository_owner, '/', repository_name) AS repository,
    created_at,
    merged_at, 
    extract(epoch from (merged_at - created_at)) / (3600.00 *24) as days
FROM pull_requests 
WHERE merged_at IS NOT NULL

SELECT
    repository,
    number,
    CONCAT(repository, '/pull/', number) AS label,
    event,
    time
    FROM (
        SELECT
        CONCAT(repository_owner, '/', repository_name) AS repository,
        number,
        created_at AS created_datetime,
        merged_at AS merged_datetime,
        CASE
            WHEN merged_at IS NOT NULL THEN NULL
            ELSE closed_at
        END AS closed_datetime,
        closed_at,
        merged_at
        FROM pull_requests) t
    JOIN LATERAL (
        VALUES('created', t.created_datetime), ('closed', t.closed_datetime), ('merged', t.merged_datetime)) s(event, time) ON TRUE

SELECT id, created_at, to_char(date_trunc('month', created_at), 'YYYY-MM')
FROM pull_requests

SELECT id, CONCAT(repository_owner, '/', repository_name) AS repository, created_at, merged_at, merged_at - created_at as time_to_merge
FROM pull_requests 
WHERE merged_at IS NOT NULL

SELECT CONCAT(repository_owner, '/', repository_name) AS repository,
    CASE WHEN merged_at IS NOT NULL THEN 'merged'
        WHEN closed_at IS NOT NULL THEN 'closed'
    END AS resolution_type
FROM pull_requests
WHERE state <> 'open'

SELECT
    id,
    CONCAT(repository_owner, '/', repository_name) AS repository,
    created_at,
    merged_at, 
    extract(epoch from (merged_at - created_at)) / (3600.00 *24) as days
FROM pull_requests 
WHERE merged_at IS NOT NULL

SELECT CONCAT(repository_owner, '/', repository_name) AS repository, COUNT(merged_at) AS merged, (COUNT(closed_at) - COUNT(merged_at)) AS closed
FROM pull_requests
WHERE state <> 'open'
GROUP BY repository
